            {
                "s2_paper_id": "23731bb7e127683c74e48349fbdd7912bea7bc78",
                "title": "Theoretical Modeling of sp3 Quantum Defects in Boron Nitride",
                "year": 2023,
                "venue": "ECS Meeting Abstracts",
                "citation_count": 0,
                "reference_count": 0,
                "abstract": "Atomic defects in solids are intensively investigated as promising candidates for use as single photon sources. However, except for several remarkable exceptions, the atomic structures of these defects are largely unknown. We performed density functional theory calculations to predict SP3 quantum defects in boron nitride that can behave as bright emitters. The results point to possible new designs of quantum emitters in low-dimensional BN materials.",
